Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

So while I agree that creating a list first is expensive, we do not need to increase the difficulty of back-porting patches to stable/icehouse or stable/juno this way. We can remove the square brackets and gain a negligible performance enhancement by using generators as the parameter to a call to dict. This has been supported since 2.6 and it would make the diff between stable/{icehouse,juno} and master far easier to grok.

Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

Regarding http://paste.openstack.org/show/154798/

1. you need to initialize the list in one place as part of setup. You'll get more accurate results that way.

2. You run the test using dict() more times than you run it using a dictionary comprehension. Probably for the following reason

3. The difference between the first two results is half a *micro*second.

    1000000 loops, best of 5: 1.14 usec per loop
    1000000 loops, best of 5: 1.69 usec per loop

Granted, this can have worse performance, but you show only one run when the results suite you. You should run the dictionary comprehension timeit several times as well, with proper setup. The results are closer than you are trying to demonstrate here.
